text: The Division of Cunningham is an Australian electoral division in New South Wales. It was set up in 1949 and is named for Allan Cunningham, a 19th century explorer of New South Wales and Queensland. It is on the coast of New South Wales and includes parts of the city of Wollongong, Corrimal, Figtree and Unanderra. It also includes several suburbs of Sydney, including Heathcote and Bundeena. ==Members== Member Party Years Billy Davies Labor 1949–1956 Victor Kearney Labor 1956–1963 Rex Connor Labor 1963–1977 Stewart West Labor 1977–1993 Stephen Martin Labor 1993–2002 Michael Organ Greens 2002–2004 Sharon Bird Labor 2004–present Rex Connor was the Minister for Minerals and Energy in the Whitlam government. Stephen Martin was Speaker of the House of Representatives from 1993-1996. Sharon Bird held several ministerial positions in the Gillard and Rudd governments. ==Election results== ==References== * ==Other websites== * Division of Cunningham - Australian Electoral Commission Category:Electoral divisions of New South Wales Category:1949 establishments in Australia
